==Educational goals==
The game is designed to make younger players comfortable to their surroundings as they become absorbed in the activities,<ref>{{cite magazine |url=https://archive.org/stream/GPPCEVol5No3/GPPCE_Vol_5_No_3#page/n43 |title=The Learning Game - Ripe for Exploring |magazine=Game Players PC Entertainment |publisher=GP Publications |volume=5 |issue=3 |page=42}}</ref> helps them get ready for school<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Fax - The Playroom |url=https://archive.org/stream/Guida-Videogiochi-14#page/n5 |magazine=Guida Videogiochi |issue=14 |publisher=Jackson |date=September 1990 |page=6}}</ref> and offers them learning opportunities in a non-threatening manner.<ref name="Playroom-TWindow"/> Literacy skills are not required to play it.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Himowitz|first=Michael|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/1990-10-08/features/1990281106_1_playroom-toy-displays-mouse-hole|title=Playroom puts computers in the hands of preschoolers|work=Baltimore Sun|date=October 8, 1990|access-date=September 21, 2018|language=en}}</ref> Topics in the game include simple math, reading, time and reasoning skills.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1990/04/08/education/a-hard-look-at-software-romper-rooms.html|last=Lewis|first=Peter H.|title=A Hard Look at Software; Romper Rooms|work=New York Times|date=April 8, 1990|access-date=September 21, 2018|language=en}}</ref> It pays great attention to detail, clearly spelling out meanings to make reading letters and words plus typing easy. There are also activities to teach telling the time, counting and using imagination. The user manual also includes fun activities to add to enjoyment.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.deseretnews.com/article/137493/GAMES-FOR-KIDS-TEACH-WHILE-THEY-ENTERTAIN.html|title=Games for Kids Teach while they Entertain|work=Deseret News|access-date=September 21, 2018|language=en}}</ref> Copies of the game also came with a stuffed toy of Pepper Mouse.<ref>{{cite journal |title=Brøderbund Catalog |url=http://mocagh.org/broderbund/broderbund-catalog2.pdf |publisher=[[Brøderbund]] |page=30 |accessdate=3 June 2016}}</ref> Aided by this software, Children can learn and advance at their own pace and play in their own way.<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Raskin |first=Robin |title=The Playroom lets Children Advance at their own Pace |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ByIl6BeV7z8C&pg=PT386 |magazine=[[PC Magazine]] |volume=9 |issue=3 |publisher=[[Ziff Davis]] |date=February 13, 1990 |pages=383–384}}</ref>

