''The Playroom'' won six Early Learning Awards.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pcmuseum.ca/details.asp?id=39061&type=software |title=PC Museum - The Playroom |accessdate=September 21, 2018}}</ref> ''[[Computer Gaming World]]'' gave the game four stars out of five, calling it "clever and engaging"<ref name="rackelson199106"/> and placed it as one of the SPA Top Hits for Home Education.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://archive.org/stream/Computer_Gaming_World_Issue_94#page/n57 |title=PC Research/SPA Top Hits |magazine=[[Computer Gaming World]] |date=May 1992 |issue=94 |page=58}}</ref>

The game was reviewed in the ''[[Oppenheim Toy Portfolio Award|Oppenheim Toy Portfolio Guide Book]]'' where the authors described it as "virtual reality for three- to six-year-olds" and claimed that "[t]here is real education going on behind the scenes of this creative playroom".<ref>{{cite book |last=Oppenheim |first=Joanne and Stephanie |author-link= Oppenheim Toy Portfolio Award |title = The Best Toys, Books & Videos for Kids |publisher = [[Harper Perennial]] |series = [[Oppenheim Toy Portfolio Award|Oppenheim Toy Portfolio Guide Book]] |volume = 1 |edition = 1st |location = New York |date = 1993 |section= Computer Software/CD-ROM - Environments for Learning: 'The Playroom' |page = 272 |isbn = 0-06-273196-3}}</ref>

